nda exercises in which the victims were condemned before the proceedings even opened proving the most powerful men in the land could be brought down overnight. After thirty-five years in power Henry was a bloated hideously obese black-humored old recluse. And despite his having had six wives the Tudor dynasty rested on the slight shoulders of his only male heir the nine-year-old Prince Edward -- a situation that spurred rival factions into a deadly conflict to control the throne. The Last Days of Henry VIII is a gripping and compelling history as fascinating and remarkable as its subject.\"','The Last Days of Henry VIII',4.14,'Biography & Autobiography','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=acCmQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',2005),(289,673,'Colleen McCullough',9780060000000,'A saga of three generations of the indomitable Cleary family begins in the early 1900s when Paddy Cleary a poor New Zealand farm laborer moves his wife and children to the Australian sheep station owned by his wealthy sister in a new edition of the classic novel of forbidden love between young Meggie Cleary and Father Ralph de Bricassart. Reprint. 15000 first printing.','The Thorn Birds',4.23,'Fiction','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mtBZngEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',2005),(290,464,'Simon Winchester',9780060000000,'Simon Winchester New York Times bestselling author of The Professor and the Madman examines the legendary annihilation in 1883 of the volcano-island of Krakatoa which was followed by an immense tsunami that killed nearly forty thousand people. The effects of the immense waves were felt as far away as France. Barometers in BogotÃ¡ and Washington D.C. went haywire. Bodies were washed up in Zanzibar. The sound of the island\'s destruction was heard in Australia and India and on islands thousands of miles away. Most significant of all -- in view of today\'s new political climate -- the eruption helped to trigger in Java 